* Description

This is data-quality pipeline of MIRCX.
We use it to explore the performances of the detectors.

* Requirements

python3 in anaconda3
some packages (all from anaconda3)

* Usage

Make sure the mircx_pipeline is located in a directory
pointed out by your $PYTHONPATH variable.

Go in the directory you want to reduce, run the script:

  bin/mircx_preproc.py

Look at output products in ./reduced/


